{{Quote|Wow! Are these towers ''trees'', Mira?''"<br />"''No, Luke&hellip;''gigantic fungus''! The thickest, wildest forest on Kessel!|[[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] and [[Mira Volz]]|<ref name="The Second Kessel Run" />}}
The '''Giant Fungi Forest''',<ref name="The Second Kessel Run" /> also known as the '''Great Fungi Forest''', was a titanic patch<ref name="The Unseen Planets of Star Wars">{{InsiderCite|36|The Unseen Planets of Star Wars|The Unseen Planets of ''Star Wars''}}</ref> of huge, trumpet-shaped [[Fungus/Legends|fungi]]<ref name="giant fungi forest">{{CSWECite|I|340|giant fungi forest}}</ref> located on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Little Kessel]].<ref name="The Second Kessel Run" /><ref name="The Essential Atlas" /> They were large and strong enough for the world's [[Kesselian|inhabitants]] to build homes and offices inside of them. Several of the large<ref name="giant fungi forest" /> [[Mushroom/Legends|mushrooms]]<ref name="The Unseen Planets of Star Wars" /> were even used as landing pads.<ref name="giant fungi forest" /> [[Professor/Legends|Professor]] [[Renn Volz]] did [[Gender/Legends|his]] most advanced research in a [[Volz Complex|laboratory]] hidden in the stipe of one of the [[Forest/Legends|forest's]] gigantic fungus.<ref name="The Second Kessel Run" />

In the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]],<ref name="TNEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Bzorn]] of the [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Imperial Navy]], under personnel orders by [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] to located and punish planets sympathetic to the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]], commandeered Volz's [[Ionic Ring Ship]]. When Little Kessel's government refused to surreneder its Rebels, Bzorn [[Devastation of Little Kessel|attacked]] the Giant Fungi Forest using [[Groundquake/Legends|earthquakes]], which the world had not experienced for eons.<ref name="The Second Kessel Run" />

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|Russ Manning, the original writer of the syndicated ''Star Wars'' newsparer strip, penned "The Second Kessel Run" not long after the first movie was released. The rather hackneyed storyline involved the Empire's use of a giant weather-control machine to cow the peaceful Kesselians, whose lush, verdant homeworld housed a titanic mushroom patch called the Great Fungi Forest. Why Threepio would be terrified of being sent to a planet that looked like a paradisical Shangri-La was left unexplained.|[[Daniel Wallace]]|<ref name="The Unseen Planets of Star Wars" />}}
The Giant Fungi Forest was originally created for the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] [[Star Wars (comic strip)|newspaper comic strip]] ''[[The Second Kessel Run]]'', written by [[Russ Helm]] and penciled by [[Russ Manning]], which ran from [[January 1]] to [[February 25]], [[1980]].<ref name="The Second Kessel Run" />

